    &lt;CommentText&gt;I went for my shoulder operation at Stepping Hill hospital recently. I was on ward M4. I would like to thank all the staff , doctors and nurses who looked after me since admission to discharge.  
Harriet staff nurse was very pleasant. I donâ€™t remember seeing any doctors post surgery but I was too sleepy. Regi on the ward looked after me well giving me water, pillow etc.  
The only observation I would like to mention is the bell outside the ward is not answered for long time, my husband was waiting for 10-15 minutes to pick me and he said the staff who finally let him in was very curt. There were people waiting before him to go in the ward.There is a waiting area to sit at reception before entry to ward but is not used, the bell could be moved to the ward door as elderly relatives could sit down if staff is busy. Staff mentioned they cannot hear the buzzer if working towards the end of the ward.&lt;/CommentText&gt;
